## Task 3 — OS Interaction and Landscape

### OS Interfaces

**GUI (Graphical User Interface)**
* Visual representation of the system — icons, windows, menus
* Familiar and intuitive — no syntax required
* Analogy: tapping a destination in a navigation app

**CLI (Command-Line Interface)**
* Text-based commands to retrieve or manipulate information
* More precise, faster for advanced tasks, requires command knowledge
* Analogy: entering exact GPS coordinates — direct and accurate if you know the syntax

Both can retrieve the same information. The choice depends on context and complexity of the task.

### Operating System Types

| OS Type | Primary use case | Key characteristics |
|---|---|---|
| Desktop | Personal computers, daily work, gaming | Rich GUI, multitasking, user-focused |
| Server | Web hosting, databases, cloud, back-end | Headless (no GUI), maximum uptime, multi-user, remote access |
| Mobile | Smartphones and tablets | Touch UI, power efficient, always connected, app sandboxing |
| Embedded | Appliances, cars, IoT, routers | Tiny footprint, limited hardware |
| Virtual / Cloud | VMs, containers, cloud instances | Lightweight, scalable, rapid deployment |

